                            <comment id="96639" author="cndoublehero" created="Wed, 18 Dec 2013 02:55:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;because you didn&apos;t add a csrf token when you post your data.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="96658" author="shawnim" created="Wed, 18 Dec 2013 09:40:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for looking at this. I was surprised that csrf was on by default when using basic auth. Adding csrf().disable() resolved this for me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="97015" author="rwinch" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 13:07:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CSRF is enabled by default with Java Configuration to be as secure as possible by default. XML configuration requires explicit configuration right now to remain passive, but will be on by default in 4.0. Resolving as invalid per discussion&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
